Can you provide 2 exercise plan for my weight losing goal?

Sure, here are two sample exercise plans that you can consider as part of your weight loss journey:
Plan 1: High-Intensity Interval Training (HIIT)
Warm-up: 5-10 minutes of light cardio (jogging, jumping jacks, etc.)

Sprints: 3 sets of 30 seconds of all-out sprinting, followed by 30 seconds of rest. Repeat for a total of 10-15 minutes.
Strength Training: 3 sets of 8-12 reps of the following exercises:
Squats
Lunges
Push-ups
Dumbbell rows
Planks (hold for 30-60 seconds)
Cardio: 30 minutes of moderate-intensity aerobic exercise (jogging, cycling, swimming, etc.)
Cool-down: 5-10 minutes of stretching
Plan 2: Bodyweight Circuit Training
Warm-up: 5-10 minutes of light cardio (jogging, jumping jacks, etc.)

Squats: 3 sets of 12 reps
Push-ups: 3 sets of 12 reps
Lunges: 3 sets of 12 reps (6 per leg)
Planks: 3 sets of 60-second hold
Bicycle crunches: 3 sets of 12 reps
Russian twists: 3 sets of 12 reps (6 per side)
Wall sit: 3 sets of 60-second hold
Cool-down: 5-10 minutes of stretching
Remember to always listen to your body and start slowly, especially if you're new to exercise. It's important to set realistic goals and gradually increase the intensity and duration of your workouts as you get stronger and more comfortable. Also, make sure to consult with a doctor or fitness professional before starting any new exercise program.

Also provide some breakfast recipe

Sure! Here are two healthy breakfast recipes that can help you lose weight:
Recipe 1: Avocado and Egg Toast
Ingredients:

2 slices of whole grain bread
1 ripe avocado, mashed
2 eggs, cooked to your liking
Salt and pepper to taste
Instructions:
Toast the bread until it's lightly browned.
Spread the mashed avocado on top of the toast.
Crack the eggs on top of the avocado and season with salt and pepper.
Cook the eggs until they're cooked to your liking, then fold them into the avocado.
Serve and enjoy!
Recipe 2: Greek Yogurt and Berries Parfait
Ingredients:
1 cup of Greek yogurt (plain or flavored)
1/2 cup of mixed berries (such as blueberries, strawberries, raspberries)
1 tablespoon of honey or maple syrup (optional)
Instructions:
Layer the Greek yogurt, mixed berries, and honey or maple syrup in a bowl.
Mix well and enjoy!
Tips:
Use low-fat or non-fat milk or yogurt to reduce calories and fat content.
Choose unsweetened almond milk or other plant-based milk alternatives for a dairy-free option.
Experiment with different types of berries, such as frozen mixed berries or fresh raspberries, for added flavor and nutrition.
Remember to drink plenty of water throughout the day to stay hydrated and support weight loss.
